<br>
It soon became appearant that The Protector was healing the Dragon and he could not be attacked in turn. This did not deter the good (and evil) people of our fair land from doing their all to take them down. A short while later the Focus began to taunt us in earnest. He claimed that our most powerful were but puppets compared to the might of their dragon lord and that if we did not trust in our weaker comrades then we were truely lost and we had no hope of victory. That's when I figured it was time to do what I had to do. <br>
<br>
I put out the battle cry and waded into combat with the tiny little goblin known as the Focus. Spear and club in hand and a whistful song on my tongue, I gave it my all. Alas, it was of little use. try as I might, I could barely scratch the annoying little pest and was soon put to rest (#2). <br>
<br>
And lo, I find myself in the Plane of Knowledge. This was the perfect opportunity and I took advantage of it. I shouted out for all to hear the news of the beast rampageing across the lake of ill omen. I called out for all of our weaker breatheren to come to our aid. I barely had a moment to catch my breath when my soul was yanked back to my resting place. <br>
<br>
I grabbed up my weapons and a bit of armor and went back to work on the Focus. He said to me that I was wasteing my time and that there was not hope. He gloated that he and his deathknight friends had killed me twice and would do so again. I just laughed at him. He didn't know what I knew. I told him that he could kill me a thousand times, but as long as the hearts of those around me held true, we would be victorious. My battle songs sounded off deaf ears, but my spear and club were enough annoyance for his bodyguards to give me an occational swat. But I had more help than any humble bard could ever hope for. All around me the heros (both good and evil) fought side by side to keep my safe while I did battle with the little focus. I had no hope of defeating him by myself and despite the diligent defense of my comrades, I fell again to the floor (#3).<br>
<br>
And I was back in the Plane of Knowledge. I shouted out again to all that would listen that there was a mighty force of destruction in lake of ill omen and that without their aid, we were at a stalemate. And again, I was yanked back to the place of my demise. Again I picked up the weapons that would make me of at least some small use and yet again, grabbed up the attention of that nasty little focus. But by this time, I was no longer alone in my fight. Others of my less that seasoned experiance were milling in by the dozens. I could see the fear in the Focus's eye as the very real possibility of defeat closed in around him. It only took a few moments for him to fall and all the knowledge of the universe could not have wiped the smile from my face. <br>
<br>
I yelled out a victory cry and shouted out to all those around me to fight on. The tide of battle had turned and there was nothing that could stop us. At this point, my part of the battle was done. I continued to do what I could to inspire and help to coordinate the flow of battle as best I could, but the mighty warrior Warz had things well in hand. There was a feeling of comraderie and teamwork flowing across the battlefield that day that will not soon be repeated. Peoples of all races and walks of life pulled together with purpose. With one goal in mind. The Protector of the dragon fell. The Tainted Deathknight fell. The other Deathknights fell. And the Dragon himself, who does not deserve to have his name mentioned, fell to this force. <br>
<br>
And there was peace again in and around the Lake of ill Omen. There was much rejoicing and merriment had by all. For my part, I only just made it back in time to watch the final fight unfold. I had been slain by (of all things) a simple goblin soothsayer. But there were clerics apleanty that were happy to help all regain what little might have been lost and all in all, it was a good day. (and yes, the Spirit of Adventure gifted me with a Mask of Tinkering. I cannot say how cool it is to be a gnome bard. The world looks like a whole new place from that perspective. hehe)<br>
